verbose_text: Furthermore, in Azotobacter vinelandii, a model bacterium containing all three metallotypes of nitrogenase, nifDK (encoding for the MoFe protein) is universally expressed in the presence of MoFe whereas vnfDGK (encoding for FeV protein) is expressed only under low Mo conditions or under cooler temperatures.
evidence: nifDK (encoding for the MoFe protein) is universally expressed
